<h1>Simple Major Keys</h1>
<p>
  This example shows a straightforward I–IV–V–I progression in F major.
  The first bar uses <code>A#</code> — a valid note name, but the wrong spelling
  for F major, where the diatonic fourth is B♭.
</p>
<p>
  Notice how the normaliser rewrites <code>A#</code> to <code>Bb</code> in the
  output. Grigson always respells chords to match the key signature, so your
  charts read the way a musician would expect on the bandstand.
</p>
